	Description of role</p>
<p>
	Software Engineer: Data Scientist</p>
<p>
	You&#39;re a software engineer.&nbsp; You love data.&nbsp; And you design great products.</p>
<p>
	Game Closure is building the world&#39;s most insightful analytics platform.&nbsp; As a data scientist, you&#39;ll study mobile games:&nbsp; What motivates a person to play a mobile game?&nbsp; What is the definition of a successful game?&nbsp; y are some games successful, while others are not?&nbsp; How do game studios make decisions, and how can we help them to make better decisions?&nbsp; Do these pique your interest?&nbsp; If so, join us!</p>
<p>
	Responsibilities</p>
<p>
	Write robust, scalable software (You&#39;re a software engineer.)<br />
	Choose the metrics to include in our suite.&nbsp; (You love data.)<br />
	Turn those metrics into insights.&nbsp; (You design great products.)</p>
<p>
	Requirements</p>
<p>
	An impressive background in software engineering.&nbsp; eg: A few years in industry, a really cool open-source project, or a CS degree.<br />
	Fluency in one of our core languages (Python, JavaScript, Java).<br />
	An eye for product: you&#39;re not writing one-off analysis: you&#39;re building the world&#39;s most insightful analytics platform.<br />
	Familiarity with the usual tools (MapReduce, SQL, distributed hash tables, REST APIs).</p>
