	<strong>Job Description: Full-time Senior Web Developer</strong><br />
	Come join the team of SDK Mobile Publishing Tools at Game Closure, where we are building the world&#39;s most advanced HTML5 game engine. You will work on tools to help our customer game studios understand their player demographics, and help them to optimize user acquisition and marketing efforts. These tools are crucial to the success of our customers&rsquo; mobile games and a core part of our product. This position involves working closely with the analytics and game engine teams, so our ideal candidates would be smart, passionate, and well-rounded engineers.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Required Qualifications</strong><br />
	We are relatively technology agnostic from project to project, but there is currently a large focus on Python, node.js, MySQL, and MongoDB on the back-end, and backbone.js, mustache, jQuery, CoffeeScript, and underscore.js on the front-end. You should be familiar with at least half of these technologies and be ready to learn new tools and languages quickly. Most importantly, you should be able to start shipping functioning code the day you join and always move quickly. BS in Computer Science or a related field is strongly preferred.</p>
<p>
	<strong>About Game Closure</strong><br />
	Game Closure is a team of 25 passionate engineers building the world&rsquo;s best mobile game engine. We believe that HTML5 is the future for games on iOS and Android, and we use any technology necessary to make this vision true today, including Python, Java, JavaScript, C, C++, Objective-C, ActionScript, Clojure, and many more. We offer competitive benefits, salary, relocation and immigration support. We are located in the fantastic area of downtown Mountain View (on Castro Street), and we are a great team of fun-loving individuals who are looking for like-minded people to join us in changing the world!</p>
